title: For Sale:  VZ.58 CNCWARRIOR Rare Rifle
postcontent:
Brand new never fired - This rifle was the last make of the CNCWarrior line of in house crafted VZ58 Rifles.I had originally purchased the rifle with the intent to SBR it sometime in the feature when legislation was passed, this rifle has been in the safe for years and unfired. The packing grease is still thereCNCWarrior VZ58Prepared to be an SBR! currently has pinned fake suppressor on rifle.Comes with Bonesteel arms quad rail systemAK47 Style Pistol GripSide folder stockRifle is parkerized6 Mags with UTG caseAVG NOT INCLUDED
Can do half on the transfer fee 
 
*Take from manufacturer websiteThe VZ58 is a very highly regarded weapon with many distinct features. It shoots the ever popular 7.62 X 39 round. It uses a direct impingement gas system and striker based trigger system, The CNC Warrior receiver and trigger group are well known for their reliability and smooth action.These guns are built from all original Czech military parts combined with brand new CNC Warrior parts for upgraded quality and US922r compliance. The barrel is shortened all the way back to the gas block, then re-faced, crowned, and threaded to original specs. The original right-side folding wire frame buttstock is keyed into the receiver and attached with a single screw.A Bonesteel Arms Quad Rail is added to the for-end. This handguard is designed by Chris Bonesteel and manufactured by CNC Warrior from billet 6061 T6 aluminum. It has been a very highly sought after product since our initial run over two years ago. They are very popular and limited production makes them hard to find at any price. The original bakelight pistol grip and for-end are also included with this rifle for added customer value and versatility.The original military VZ58 barrels come in just under 16" in length. So a muzzle device has to be permanently attached even if the barrel was not shortened further. So we shorten it back to the gas block and permanently attach (with blind pin) a fake suppressor to reach just beyond the 16" legal barrel length. This gives the gun a great look and allows easy transitioning into a short barrel rifle if desired.

title: For Sale:  Kahr CW380 .380ACP Pocket Pistol
postcontent:
The CW380 pistol has a 2.58 inch barrel, an overall length of 4.96 inches and a height of just 3.9 inches. It weighs just 10.2 ounces without a magazine. The pistol has a black polymer frame and features 4140 steel inserts molded into the front and back of the frame for added rigidity. It has a machined, solid 416 matte stainless steel slide and a textured polymer grip.
The Kahr CW380 features a lock breech, modified Browning type recoil lug, and utilizes Kahr's seven patents including the "safe cam" action found in all Kahr pistols. The result is a micro-compact pistol with very little recoil and quick follow-up shots. The pistol features drift adjustable white bar-dot combat rear sight and pinned-in polymer front sight.
Differences between the Kahr CW380 and Kahr P380 models include: the CW series has a conventional rifled barrel instead of the match grade polygonal barrel found on P models; the CW slide stop lever is MIM (metal-injection-molded) instead of machined; the CW series slide has fewer machining operations, and uses simple roll marking instead of engraved markings; the P380 comes with two magazines, but the CW series comes with one 6 rd steel magazine with flush baseplate. Lastly, the slide locks back after firing the last round – another feature missing on a number of other value-priced compact semi-auto pistols. The durability and reliability of the CW380 model makes it a strong consideration as a backup gun for law enforcement.
